The paper deals with neural dependency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses a BiLSTM, which is a common tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of language properties on the performance of the model, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the language properties are related to visual data.
